## Validation Steps Performed

you can go to the `runner` function and supply something like this for local experimentation:

```cpp
        Trace::EventLaunch(get_product_version(), isProcessElevated);
        std::thread{[] {
          Sleep(5000);
          const wchar_t TOAST_TAG[] = L"SOMETAG!";
          notifications::toast_params params{TOAST_TAG, false};
          notifications::show_toast_with_activations(L"MSG#1 @_@", L"TITLE#1", {}, {}, std::move(params));
          while(1)
          {
              Sleep(3000);
              notifications::update_toast_contents(TOAST_TAG, L"MSG#2 #_#", L"TITLE#2");
              Sleep(3000);
              notifications::update_toast_contents(TOAST_TAG, L"MSG#3 %_%", L"TITLE#3");
          }
        }}.detach();
```
don't forget that you need to have an installed PT version (not necessarily with the same runner) for toasts to work

